A letter to users\n Welcome to use Tiantian recitation question. Nice to meet you here!\n Dear users, reciting questions every day is an app dedicated to helping you brush questions for the exam. We hope to create an ad free, excellent experience and safe storage app to give you the greatest help in the exam.\n In order to facilitate the management of test questions, we divide the content into four levels: courses, books, test papers and test questions. The test questions are the core, and you also need to edit them in word, and then import them into the test papers.\n At present, we support five types of questions: fill in the blank, judge, single choice, multiple choice, and question and answer. Each type of question has two modes of learning and memory.\n Fill in the blanks and question and answer questions currently do not support manual input and comparison of answers. You can silently recite the answers in your heart and click the answer button to compare.\n Judgement questions, single choice questions and multiple-choice questions all support direct selection of answers and comparison with accurate answers\ \N in addition to supporting various types of questions, we also make a simple statistics on your learning records. The number of daily learning questions will be displayed on the right side of the title bar, which is convenient for you to plan your learning.\n Reciting questions every day not only supports text questions, but also supports mixed arrangement of pictures and texts. All you need to do is insert the required pictures into the word document.\n In order to make it convenient for you to manage the questions, a wastebasket is also set up for reciting the questions every day. The questions you delete will be put in the wastebasket first. When you need to retrieve the wrongly deleted questions, you can recover them from the wastebasket. Of course, if you delete the title in the wastebasket, it cannot be restored.\n At the same time, there is a backup function for reciting questions every day, which backs up all the test questions in your app at a certain time in the SD card for subsequent recovery and backup. However, due to the risks brought by your device environment and the upgrade of APP version, we still hope you can save the word document in case of need.\n Finally, I wish you success in your exam!
